The paper discusses models of document coherence and their application to information retrieval, which suggests that it could belong to the sub-categories of computational linguistics (cs.CL), information retrieval (cs.IR), or machine learning (cs.LG). The use of entropy and graph-based models also suggests a potential fit with artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and social and information networks (cs.SI).
